                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_291">Manāẓir al-inshā’</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_291">مناظر الانشاء</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on the art of formal and refined epistolary composition by the great Bahmanid minister, Maḥmūd ibn Muḥammad Gīlānī (d. 886/1481) </p>
                        <p>The work consists of a muqaddimah, seven faṣl on figures of speech,  followed by several maqāmah divided into five manāẓir, concluding with a khātimah on the rules of Arabic and Persian spelling </p>
                        <p>Not dated; circa eighteenth century </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
